.TH GESSO 1 "Wayland" "gesso" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gesso \- deterministic Wayland wallpaper controller

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gesso
.RI [ options ] " <command> [command-options]"

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.

.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help information and exit.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gesso
is a deterministic Wayland wallpaper controller and daemon designed for
smooth transitions, predictable timing, and low idle memory usage.

It uses the wlr-layer-shell protocol to render wallpapers on a dedicated
background layer per output. gesso supports image and solid-colour wallpapers
with optional animated transitions.

Unlike compositor-driven wallpaper tools, gesso explicitly controls timing,
buffering, and frame pacing to avoid stalls, runaway animations, or
unbounded memory retention.

Wayland-only. Requires a compositor that supports wlr-layer-shell.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B set
Set an image wallpaper.

.TP
.B colour
Set a solid colour wallpaper.

.TP
.B unset
Unset the wallpaper on one output or all outputs.

.TP
.B outputs
List detected outputs and geometry.

.TP
.B info
Show current wallpaper state per output.

.TP
.B doctor
Run environment and compositor diagnostics.

.TP
.B stop
Stop the wallpaper daemon.

.SH IMAGE COMMAND

.B gesso set
.I target
.RI [ options ]

Set an image wallpaper. The target may be a path or a name resolved via
GESSO_DIRS.

.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mode " <fill|fit|stretch|center|tile>"
Image scaling mode. Default is
.BR fill .

.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-colour " <hex>"
Background fill colour used for letterboxing with
.B fit
or
.B center
modes.

.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-transition " <none|drop|fade|wave>"
Transition type. Default is
.BR none .

.B drop
is a hard expanding circle from the center.

.B fade
is a cross-dissolve.

.B wave
is a directional wipe with optional wave modulation.

.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-from " <left|right>"
Direction for
.B wave
transitions. Default is
.BR left .

.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-duration " <milliseconds>"
Duration of the transition in milliseconds.

This controls animation time, not frame count.
gesso dynamically paces frames to maintain smoothness under compositor load.

.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-transition-steps " <N>"
Quantize the transition into
.I N
discrete steps. If omitted or 0, the transition is smooth.

Useful for stylized or stepped animations.

.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " <name>"
Target a specific output by
.B wl_output.name
(e.g. DP-1, HDMI-A-1).

.SH COLOUR COMMAND

.B gesso colour
.I colour
.RI [ options ]

Set a solid colour wallpaper.

.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-transition " <none|drop|fade|wave>"
Transition type. Default is
.BR none .

.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-from " <left|right>"
Direction for
.B wave
transitions. Default is
.BR left .

.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-duration " <milliseconds>"
Transition duration in milliseconds.

.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-transition-steps " <N>"
Quantize the transition into
.I N
steps. Omitted or 0 means smooth.

.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " <name>"
Target a specific output.

.SH UNSET COMMAND

.B gesso unset
.RI [ output ]

Unset the wallpaper. If no output is specified, all outputs are unset.

.SH OUTPUTS COMMAND

.B gesso outputs

List all detected outputs with resolution and scale.

.SH INFO COMMAND

.B gesso info

Show current wallpaper target, mode, and transition state for each output.

.SH ENVIRONMENT

.TP
.B WAYLAND_DISPLAY
Must be set. gesso is Wayland-only.

.TP
.B GESSO_DIRS
Colon-separated list of directories used to resolve image targets that
are not absolute or relative paths.

Example:
.RS
export GESSO_DIRS="$HOME/Pictures/Wallpapers:/usr/share/backgrounds"
.RE

.TP
.B GESSO_SOCKET
Optional override for the daemon IPC socket path.

.SH DESIGN NOTES

gesso prioritizes deterministic timing and explicit control.

Transitions are time-based and bounded. When idle, buffers are released
and pixel memory is not retained unnecessarily.

If compositor frame callbacks stall, gesso continues safely rather than
deadlocking.

Silence is a feature. Failure modes are explicit.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wayland (7),
.BR wlroots (7)

